an></li><li class="c2"><span class="c27 c3">9mm H&amp;K Glock </span><span class="c27 c3 c15">OR</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;S&amp;W .357 Magnum.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c0">Any primary firearm, except for the ABF-Issue Machine Gun or the SG1.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c0">Any amount of Non-lethal grenades.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c0">Any amount of Lethal grenades.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c0">Commander&rsquo;s Uniform.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c34"><td class="c35" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">SeC</span></p><p class="c25"><span class="c54 c3">(Sectorial)</span></p></td><td class="c16" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_usifc6i60abi-0 start"><li class="c2"><span class="c0">Event Character</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c0">Access to anything.</span></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3"><br></span><a id="id.hbk189nvxcua"></a><span class="c8 c3">Designated &ldquo;Grouping&rdquo; for each Rank</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c6 c3 c22"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c3 c15 c22">Ground Unit:</span><span class="c48 c3 c15">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;i5-EpU</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c15 c47 c22">Field Command:</span><span class="c48 c3 c15">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;i1-EpU</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c15 c22 c79">Field Marshal:</span><span class="c64 c15 c79">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="c3 c15 c64">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class="c31 c64 c3">Designated Unit </span><span class="c31 c3">(On par with &ldquo;Command&rdquo;)</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c15 c22 c66">Command:</span><span class="c48 c3 c15">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;OfC-DvL</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c15 c22 c68">High Command:</span><span class="c48 c3 c15">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CmD, SeC and up.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><a id="id.va1fzer54tcx"></a><h2 class="c4 c76" id="h.lbjnkohhv0mi"><span class="c3 c15 c20">Radio Codes</span></h2><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c3">Radio codes are used so that citizens cannot decipher what is going on, preventing information leaks.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c6 c29"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-00:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Officer Down, All Patrols Respond.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-0:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Caution/Use Caution.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-1:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Not Understood.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-2:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Negative.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-3:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Radio Channel Intercepted/Stop Transmitting</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-4:</span><span class="c3">&nbsp;Copy/Copy That/Affirmative/Understood</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-7:</span><span class="c3">&nbsp;Out of Standardized Service, Unspecified Reason.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-8:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;In service/On Duty.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-9:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Repeat Message/Transmission.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-12:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Citizens/Civilians Present.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-19:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Moving to location, returning to a post.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-20:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Location.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-21:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Communication Device (Radio, Telephone, Et cetera).</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-21A:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Requesting Nexus/LEADER/Commanding Officer Advisement.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-31:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Crime in progress.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-32:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Individual with firearm.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-45:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Condition of patient.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-45a:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Condition of patient - Good</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-45b:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Condition of patient - Serious</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-45c:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Condition of patient - Critical&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-45d:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Condition of patient - Dead</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c6 c3">10-50: Patrol, Patrol in Progress. </span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-54:</span><span class="c3">&nbsp;Possible dead body.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-55:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Dead Body/DB/Corpse.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-56:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Suicide.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-56a:</span><span class="c3">&nbsp;Suicide attempt.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-55:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Dead Body/Corpse.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-55d:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Send cremator.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-60:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Lock-Out/Lock-Down.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-66:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Suspicious Individual.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-76:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Enroute/Inbound.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-80:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;In pursuit.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-90:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Active alarm.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c6 c3">10-91: Citizen.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-93:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Blockage.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c6 c3">10-99: Officer is in Need of Assistance/Officer Under Fire.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c6 c3">10-103M: Mentally Disabled, Disturbance by Mentally Disabled/Deranged Person.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-103P:</span><span class="c3">&nbsp;</span><span class="c3 c15">Physically Disabled, Disturbance </span><span class="c3 c15">by Physically</span><span class="c6 c3">&nbsp;Disabled Person.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-112:</span><span class="c3">&nbsp;Impersonating an officer.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">10-1000:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Homicide/Policide, Dead Body Confirmed.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c6 c3">10-2000: Reinforcements Required Immediately.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c6 c3"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">11-6:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Discharge of a firearm.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">11-7:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Sneaking Individual</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">11-10:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;File a Report, Report</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3 c15">11-14:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Violent Animal/Virome/Parasitic/Exogen/Et cetera.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c6 c3">11-58: Radio Transmissions being Monitored, Decommission Frequency.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c6 c3">11-86: Bomb/Explosive Threat.</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c6 c3">11-99: Officer requires immediate Assistance.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c6 c3"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c6 c3"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c6 c3"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c6 c3"></span></p><h2 class="c4 c76" id="h.j6afgb742r33"><span class="c20 c3 c15">Code Words</span></h2><a id="t.328c87d360d267047d6e8f1bef49d48f3e6f6b77"></a><a id="t.2"></a><table class="c10"><tbody><tr class="c34"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c48 c3 c15">Codeword</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c48 c3 c15">Definition/Protocole and circumstances.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c55"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">Midnight</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Applicable to a patrol, squadron/team or entire network.</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Midnight is announced over radio before activation.</span></p><p class="c12 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Description: Cease radio communications and do not speak. Use hands signals until contact or stealth has been broken. The person who calls Midnight must also call it off when done.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c84"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">Sword</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Switch to lethal firearms.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c34"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">Pacify</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Use-non lethal tactics. (Batons, etc.)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c50"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">Unrest</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Rebellion or Riot.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c50"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Anti-Citizen</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c3">Individual</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;convicted of multiple anti-civil violations; a full anti civil status.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c50"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Malignant </span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c3">Individuals convicted of multiple anti-civil violations. Subject is contagious and contains devised behavioral </span><span class="c3">pattern</span><span class="c1">.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c37"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Administer</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To issue a verdict to a resident. (e.g. Administering a beating.)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c97"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Clamp</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Restrict access to an area, or to hold a position. (e.g. a store, an apartment, the quarantine zone.)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c65"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Expose</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To expose subjects from cover. (i.e to flank or grenade a position.)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c65"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Stand By</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Await orders.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c65"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Dagger</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Bullet.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c50"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Breach</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To force entry to a designated area, often used in sweeps when breaches are placed or the door is kicked in. (Prep, Lock and Inject.)</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c50"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Stabilize</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c3">To restore order to a situation by any means necessary, this is determined lethal/</span><span class="c3">nonlethal</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;by your commanding authority.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c65"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Intercede</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Take immediate control of the situation; Ambush/surprise hostiles.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Amputate</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c3">To kill or execute a target.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Isolate</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To isolate citizens from each other, or to tell them to move away.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Vacate</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To vacate an area.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Shield</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To hold, or defend a point.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Valkyrie </span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Amputate Combine Civil Authority officers of malignant order.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Assemble</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c3">To regroup forces at specified </span><span class="c3">point</span><span class="c1">.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Pressure</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To apply suppressive fire on a target.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Sterilize</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">To resolve anti-civil activity.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c53"><td class="c44" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c45"><span class="c6 c3">Ripcord</span></p></td><td class="c19" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Return to safety.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c3 c8"></span></p><a id="id.h71p7imytjh1"></a><h2 class="c4 c76" id="h.z0c0j5i8vyhj"><span class="c20 c3 c15">Sociostatus</span></h2><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c15 c22 c85">Green:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Status is clear, everything is functioning normally and there is miniscule down effects in the city. Units may patrol normally, and may be at ease. Sidearms may only be drawn if needed.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c15 c22 c86">Yellow:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Proceed with caution. A ground unit or ground command may have been harmed. Violence and or discourse is flowing through the city. Sidearms are permitted to be drawn at all times, and those granted may have their primaries out. Deal with the situation quickly and effectively.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c68 c64 c15 c22">Red:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Danger. A command unit has been injured or harmed, or the City has a massive uptake in violence, multiple active dangerous Anti-citizens. Move with extreme caution and with lethality. Overwatch may be deployed, and primaries are issued to every unit. Further steps may be taken if necessary.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c64 c3 c15 c22">Black:</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;Use extreme prejudice and hyper lethality. Do anything possible to revert socio stability. Overwatch have taken full authority, and synthetic Universal Union soldiers are moving through the streets (i.e. Hunters/Striders.) Metropolice have either corrupted, lost a High Command unit or face extremely dangerous odds.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c8 c3"></span></p><a id="id.w903hb7scjyx"></a><h2 class="c4 c76" id="h.daeh0649pohv"><span class="c20 c3 c15">Loyalist chart and Information</span></h2><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Loyalists are to wear their loyalist armbands on their right arm. This is to be told to every citizen whenever they achieve a certain tier. Loyalists are tools of the union, their work is important to the CCA&rsquo;s cause of maintaining social stability. This means they can report crimes where the CCA may have blind spots. Each tier gains a bit more respect, but will never be seen as above a unit. </span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><a id="t.2458b28f3e5dde252dbd1a78a2ba05486b72d92e"></a><a id="t.3"></a><table class="c10"><tbody><tr class="c26"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c74">Anti-Citizen</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c74">-20 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_pp5e52p3wxf-0 start"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Enemies of the Universal Union.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Authorized to amputate.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c77"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c69 c9">Malignant</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c69">-10 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_26xff2mcqlnm-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Viewed as sub-human, treated as such.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Denied basic health care and needs.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Minimal grade rations.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c77"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c3">Standard Citizen</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c3">0 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_9s50wojecm6e-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Viewed as a standard citizen.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">No perks.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Standard grade rations.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c77"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c14">Yellow Armband</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c14 c9">5 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_6tx7j0e5xl7c-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c3">Viewed as a loyalist of the Universal Union.</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;[It should be reinforced that being a low-tier loyalist is effectively a meaningless participation trophy.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c3">Eligible for CWU employment.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c55"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c61">Green Armband</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c61 c9">15 LP</span></p><p class="c12 c5"><span class="c71 c9 c3"></span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_qvmaeul4lmca-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Receives a loyalist ration.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Eligible for CCA application.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c3">Given a Request Device</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c72"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c42 c9">Blue Armband</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c42">25 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_neww9d36c6ni-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Active citizen of the Universal Union.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Loyalist housing.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c3">Receives a loyalist ration and a standard grade ration.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c26"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c63">Purple Armband</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c63 c9">35 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_wtheyachwgeq-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Receives two loyalist grade rations.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c55"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c60">Red Armband</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c60 c9">50 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_554w8jx11qbw-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c3">Priority citizen, a citizen of notable worth.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Access to luxury UU food and recreational goods.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c3">Receives two loyalist grade rations and a standard grade ration.</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr class="c26"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c74">Black Armband</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c74">100 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_sd138nded4fa-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Receives a priority grade ration and a loyalist grade ration.</span></li></ul><p class="c12 c5 c88"><span class="c1"></span></p></td></tr><tr class="c26"><td class="c78" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c92">Gold Armband</span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c92">200 LP</span></p></td><td class="c24" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_ot09z3kt4oqx-0 start"><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Citizen of the highest standard.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">Receives two priority grade rations and a loyalist grade ration.</span></li><li class="c7"><span class="c1">May apply for the Universal Union Administration.</span></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c20 c3 c15"></span></p><a id="id.qc28xqa56eqa"></a><h2 class="c4 c76" id="h.34h3gmyiv8l"><span class="c20 c3 c15">Distribution of Loyalty Points</span></h2><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Loyalist points are based on a civilian&#39;s productive and helpful actions towards the CCA and UU. Loyalty points are a reward based system which enables civilians to achieve a better life. There are many ways of earning Loyalty points. Here is a chart that is recommended to follow when awarding points.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">It&rsquo;s highly recommended to follow the chart below on rewards. Additionally, units may offer rewards at their own discretion.</span></p><a id="t.535e7d28254de82d97faf6d3ba37328af13727d4"></a><a id="t.4"></a><table class="c10"><tbody><tr class="c89"><td class="c41" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Performing a help desk task. (Cleaning, painting, spreading UU brochures.)</span></p></td><td class="c57" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">1 LP</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c18"><td class="c41" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Reporting a petty crime.</span></p></td><td class="c57" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">3 LP</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c18"><td class="c41" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Reporting a possible mugging or attack on a unit.</span></p></td><td class="c57" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">3 LP</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c90"><td class="c41" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Reporting a high crime.</span></p></td><td class="c57" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c3 c6">5 LP</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c34"><td class="c41" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Assisting a unit in a struggle. (Giving directions, assisting with an arrest.)</span></p></td><td class="c57" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">4 LP</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c34"><td class="c41" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Saving a unit&rsquo;s life. (Taking a bullet, trying to take down an individual in an ongoing attack.)</span></p></td><td class="c57" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">6 LP</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c34"><td class="c41" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Saving the City Administrator&rsquo;s life.</span></p></td><td class="c57" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c25"><span class="c6 c3">10 LP</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><h2 class="c4 c76" id="h.s13ml5miav8k"><span>Offenses and Punishment</span><a id="kix.qjnlmisfp8mv"></a></h2><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c28"></span></p><a id="t.499105dcbe2dd5ab612fcbcf7c83a4e5fb7ca042"></a><a id="t.5"></a><table class="c10"><tbody><tr class="c34"><td class="c56" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c3">Violation Type</span></p></td><td class="c52" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c3">Violation Level</span></p></td><td class="c40" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c3">Actions</span></p></td><td class="c46" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c3">Punishment</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c34"><td class="c43" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c3">Misdemeanor</span></p></td><td class="c52" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c3">Level 1</span></p></td><td class="c40" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_pp5e52p3wxf-0"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Running.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Jumping.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Climbing.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Yelling.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Loitering.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Wasting an officer&rsquo;s time.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Uncivil behavior.</span></li></ul></td><td class="c46" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c3">On the spot re-education.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c11"><td class="c43" colspan="1" rowspan="3"><p class="c12"><span class="c71 c9 c3">Petty Violation</span></p></td><td class="c52" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c3 c9">Level 2</span></p></td><td class="c40" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_pp5e52p3wxf-0"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Wearing unauthorized clothing.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Possession of level 1 contraband.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Disobeying an officer in an inconsequential situation.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Public indecency.</span></li></ul></td><td class="c46" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c3">-2 LP and moderate re-education.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c11"><td class="c52" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c3">Level 3</span></p></td><td class="c40" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_w66jqd7u6li7-0 start"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Failing to report an in-action crime.</span></li></ul><ul class="c30 lst-kix_20ebtrwsxzhs-0 start"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Disobeying an officer in a consequential situation.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Theft.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Refusing to apply.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Possession of level 2 contraband.</span></li></ul></td><td class="c46" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c3">-4 LP, one cycle in detainment, and moderate re-education.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c83"><td class="c52" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c3">Level 4</span></p></td><td class="c40" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_20ebtrwsxzhs-0"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Trespassing on Universal Union territory, not including the sewers or nexus.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Verbally harassing an officer.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Fighting another citizen.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Resisting arrest.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c3">Refusing to answer </span><span class="c3">questioning</span><span class="c1">.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Vandalism or destruction of citizen property.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Monetary theft.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Trespassing in the metro.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Trespassing in the sewers.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Trespassing in the canals.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Trespassing in the Quarantine Zone.</span></li></ul></td><td class="c46" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c3">-6 LP, two cycles in detainment, and heavy re-education.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c11"><td class="c43" colspan="1" rowspan="3"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c3 c71">High Violation</span></p></td><td class="c52" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c3">Level 5</span></p></td><td class="c40" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_nkvrezr5fa0l-0 start"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Physical harassment of an officer. (Spitting, throwing objects, etc.)</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Anti-UU Propaganda.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Lying in questioning.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Vandalism of Universal Union property.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Possession of anti-Union propaganda.</span></li></ul></td><td class="c46" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">JUDGE trial for amputation, which has a moderate chance of passing in favor of the Universal Union.</span></p><p class="c12 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Should the trial not pass, the individual in question will receive -8 LP, three cycles in detainment, and moderate re-education.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c11"><td class="c52" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c3">Level 6</span></p></td><td class="c40" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_nkvrezr5fa0l-0"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Destruction of Universal Union property.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Procreative activity.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Trespassing inside outpost Storm.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Trespassing inside outpost Nomad.</span></li></ul><p class="c12 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p></td><td class="c46" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c1">JUDGE trial for amputation, which should easily result in passing in favor of the Universal Union.</span></p><p class="c12 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c12"><span class="c1">Should the trial not pass, the individual in question will receive -10 LP, four cycles in detainment, and heavy re-education.</span></p></td></tr><tr class="c11"><td class="c52" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c9 c3">Level 7</span></p></td><td class="c40" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><ul class="c30 lst-kix_hwzqpl2rnj3a-0 start"><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Homicide/Attempted Homicide</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Policide.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Trespassing inside the Nexus.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Possession of Level 3 contraband.</span></li><li class="c2"><span class="c1">Rebel conspiracy.</span></li></ul></td><td class="c46" colspan="1" rowspan="1"><p class="c12"><span class="c3">Immediate amputation.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c8 c66">Re-Education</span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c3">There are several forms of re-education. The most common is on the spot re-education, where the individual in question is simply struck with the stunstick 1 to 3 times, the number being at the discretion of the officer. If the citizen is to run away from the officer, the officer is to pursue for only up to 15 meters. If the individual </span><span class="c3">continues to flee, the officer is to return to their previous station. On the spot re-education is to always take plac</span><span class="c1">e on low stunstick intensity. Moderate re-education is to take place while the citizen faces a wall, with the officer&rsquo;s stunstick set to medium. The individual is to be struck 5 to 7 times, the number being at the discretion of the officer. An officer is not to search a citizen during a moderate re-education unless sociostatus is yellow or worse, a judgment waiver is in effect, or unrest procedure is in effect. Heavy re-education is also to take place on a wall, with the officer&rsquo;s stunstick set to high. It will always include a search. The individual is to be struck 4 to 6 times, the number being at the discretion of the officer.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><h2 class="c4 c76" id="h.4n7i4h127sxd"><span class="c20 c3 c15">Contraband</span></h2><p class="c4"><span class="c1">There are three levels of contraband, designated numerically from least severe to most severe. Level 1 consists of inconsequential objects, such as nonstandard clothing or non-UU-branded alcohol. Level 2 consists of possibly consequential objects such as biogel, unauthorized medication, and radios. Level 3 consists of anything that can possibly be used in combat, such as firearms, kevlar, or explosives.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c1">Due to the infinite nature of possible objects, the following list is incomplete. If there is any question as to what an object should be classified as, contact a JUDGE unit if one is available, or if no JUDGE unit is on duty, consult any command or high command unit. When a new piece of contraband is decided on, contact a command or high command unit so they may add it to the list.</span></p><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c48 c3 c15">Level 1</span></p><ul class="c30 lst-kix_fqy1afnr9p0x-0 start"><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Nonstandard Clothing</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Non-UU-Branded Alcohol</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Civil Protection Rations</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Spray Paint</span></li></ul><p class="c4 c5"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c48 c3 c15">Level 2</span></p><ul class="c30 lst-kix_pd92ovb5s6cn-0 start"><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Biogel Products</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Bleach</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Non Prescribed Drugs</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Communication-capable Radio</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Combine Worker Outfits</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Combine Lock</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Union Lock</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Civil Workers&rsquo; Union ID (When the individual is not a member of the CWU.)</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Tools</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Combine Battery</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Zip Tie</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Loyalist Armband (When the individual in question is not eligible to own the armband.)</span></li></ul><p class="c4 c5 c91"><span class="c1"></span></p><p class="c4"><span class="c48 c3 c15">Level 3</span></p><ul class="c30 lst-kix_pd92ovb5s6cn-0"><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Any Firearm</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Any Ammunition</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Any Explosive</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Kevlar Vest</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Condensed Dark Energy Charge</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Smoke Grenade</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Tear Gas Grenade</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c1">Flashbang</span></li><li class="c4 c38"><span class="c3">Breaching Charge</span></li></ul></body></html>

]]